{"type":"message","id":"5f9de078","parentId":"2d323913","timestamp":"2026-06-04T14:55:00.982Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have comprehensive information. Let me synthesize the answer.\n\nKey facts gathered:\n1. SOP-v6.0.md is the canonical documentation file at /home/halei/workspace-tts/docs/SOP-v6.0.md\n2. The three-level funnel (三级漏斗) is documented there, consisting of 3 stages (not 4 - the \"fourth\" is Feishu output):\n   - Stage 1: tiktok_product_trend (批量接口, VN+TH hair accessories)\n   - Stage 2: shopee_similar_product (VN+TH site validation)\n   - Stage 3: ali1688_similar_product (batch, profit calculation ≥40%)\n3. The workflow from the cron job prompt is slightly different from SOP - it merges stages 2+3 for S-level products and calls tiktok_product_trend with different params than the full SOP\n4. The Feishu bitable is app_token=AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd, table_id=tblHU2do30jzinJT\n\nI've collected the key details from the SOP and cron prompts. The three-level funnel is clearly defined with tiktok_product_trend as the entry point for VN+TH hair accessories, followed by shopee_similar_product validation and ali1688_similar_product for profit verification. The Feishu integration completes the workflow with the specific app token and table ID mapped out.\n\nNow I'll prepare the JSON response with this synthesized information.","thinkingSignature":"ef2c5bd4d733f93e8064167c7210d88aa8d73f34227f432eded44fbeeda2749b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n```json\n{\n  \"answer\": \"The complete v6.0 TikTok product sourcing workflow is documented in `/home/halei/workspace-tts/docs/SOP-v6.0.md`. The three-level funnel (三级漏斗) consists of three filter stages, each gated — only products passing the prior stage may enter the next:\\n\\n**Stage 1 — TikTok Hair Accessories Trend Scan**\\n- Tool: `tiktok_product_trend` (Sorftime batch API)\\n- Sites: Vietnam (VN) + Thailand (TH), category 【时尚配件>发饰】\\n- Daily quota: ≤300 calls, polled every 2 hours\\n- Filter criteria: 24h sales环比≥100% + consecutive 2-day positive growth; ≥8 new promotional videos in 24h; avg rating ≥4.2; 7-day negative review rate ≤5%; 1万-10万粉 mid-tier influencers ≥80% of new promoters; price $1.5–$8; same-product sellers ≤8; no IP-infringing designs (Disney, Sanrio, etc.); return rate ≤10%\\n- Output: Top 80 products with title, keywords, 24h/7d sales trend, new video count, rating, seller count, main image\\n- S-class emergency (skip routine): 12h sales doubled + ≥15 new videos + rating ≥4.3 → full stages 2+3 validation within 10 min\\n\\n**Stage 2 — Shopee Platform Life Cycle Validation**\\n- Tool: `shopee_similar_product` (VN+TH, keyword search by title); fallback `shopee_product_request` if no data\\n- Daily quota: ≤200 calls\\n- Must-pass: same product monthly sales ≥500, rating ≥4.2, 7-day review count growing\\n- Bonus: competitors ≤5, Shopee avg price > TikTok price by ≥15%\\n- Block: no same-product, return rate ≥12%, rating <4.0, ≥3 negative reviews with keywords \\\"易断/掉色/质量差\\\"\\n\\n**Stage 3 — 1688 Supply Chain Profit Calculation**\\n- Tool: `ali1688_similar_product` (Sorftime batch API)\\n- Daily quota: ≤350 calls\\n- Find Yiwu/Guangzhou factory source, extract lowest purchase price (MOQ ≤20), delivery ≤3 days, mixed-batch supported, Vietnam overseas warehouse labeling supported\\n- Profit formula: margin = (TikTok price − 1688 purchase price − logistics − platform commission) / TikTok price\\n- Pass threshold: margin ≥40%\\n\\n**Stage 4 (Output) — Write to Feishu Bitable**\\n- Target: app_token=AKppbAeyXanToTsVl6ScxO5QnZd, table_id=tblHU2do30jzinJT\\n- Fields: product title, main image, TikTok sales data, Shopee validation data, 1688 purchase price, margin, recommendation grade (S/A/B), entry timestamp\\n\\n**Workflow summary from cron job prompt**: 1) Call `tiktok_product_trend` scan VN+TH hair accessories, filter 24h sales环比≥100%、videos≥8、rating≥4.2、price $5–$15 (limit 30); 2) S-level products trigger stages 2+3 immediately; 3) Pass products call `ali1688_similar_product` for cost + margin (target ≥40%); 4) Write results to Feishu bitable; 5) Send selection report to Feishu.\\n\\nThe SOP correctly describes a four-stage flow (1 TikTok scan → 2 Shopee validation → 3 1688 profit check → 4 Feishu output), but internally stages 2+3 are merged for S-class emergencies. The SOP file is the authoritative source.\",\n  \"citedIds\": [\"sum_c82867b676d9434a\"],\n  \"expandedSummaryCount\": 1,\n  \"totalSourceTokens\": 1802,\n  \"truncated\": false\n}\n```"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1785,"output":1183,"cacheRead":46912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49880,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780584892056,"responseId":"0670c4bc73e6c2f8b0afe602b936c41b"}}
